article.headline: Fresno State 95, Cal Poly 75
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Hector Hernandez scored a career-high 31 points, including eight 3-pointers, as Fresno State pulled away to defeat Cal Poly 95-75 on Saturday night. Quinton Hosley had 20 points and 12 rebounds for the Bulldogs, who tied a school record with 16 3-pointers. Dominic McGuire added 17 points, nine rebounds and six assists. Kevin Bell had a career-high 13 assists for Fresno State, which improved to 10-2 in non-conference play. After trailing by as many as 24 points in the first half, the Mustangs outscored Fresno State 23-13 to begin the second half. Cal Poly pulled to within 71-67 with 7:48 left on consecutive baskets by Dawin Whiten and Dreshawn Vance before running out of steam in the closing minutes. The Mustangs fell to 5-5 with the loss and are 0-4 this season on the road.
